History[edit]




The Steelcase Corporate Development Center near Grand Rapids, Michigan: opened in 1989 at a cost of $111 million, vacated by Steelcase in 2010, sold for $7.5 million in 2014 — and as of 2016, sold to Switch as a datacenter.
42°51′08″N 85°33′37″W﻿ / ﻿42.8523°N 85.5603°W﻿ / 42.8523; -85.5603


